# OpenVideo License

OpenVideo is a framework-agnostic video editor SDK built on WebCodecs API, designed to make video editing accessible across different web frameworks and platforms.

---

Depending on the type of your legal entity, you are granted permission to use OpenVideo for your project. Individuals and small companies are allowed to use OpenVideo to create videos for free (even commercial), while a company license is required for for-profit organizations of a certain size. This two-tier system was designed to ensure funding for this project while still allowing the source code to be available and the program to be free for most. Read below for the exact terms of use.

- [Free License](#free-license)
- [Company License](#company-license)

## Free License

Copyright Â© 2025 OpenVideo

### Eligibility

You are eligible to use OpenVideo for free if you are:

- an individual
- a for-profit organization with up to 3 employees
- a non-profit or not-for-profit organization
- evaluating whether OpenVideo is a good fit, and are not yet using it in a commercial way

### Allowed use cases

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person eligible for the "Free License", to use the software non-commercially or commercially for the purpose of creating videos and images and to modify the software to their own liking, for the purpose of fulfilling their custom use case or to contribute bug fixes or improvements back to OpenVideo.

### Disallowed use cases

It is not allowed to copy or modify OpenVideo code for the purpose of selling, renting, licensing, relicensing, or sublicensing your own derivative of OpenVideo.

### Warranty notice

The software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. In no event shall the author or copyright holders be liable for any claim, damages or other liability, whether in an action of contract, tort or otherwise, arising from, out of or in connection with the software or the use or other dealings in the software.

### Support

Support is provided on a best-we-can-do basis via GitHub Issues and community forums.

## Company License

You are required to obtain a Company License to use OpenVideo if you are not within the group of entities eligible for a Free License. This license will enable you to use OpenVideo for the allowed use cases specified in the Free License, and give you access to prioritized support.

### License Benefits

- Commercial use for organizations with more than 3 employees
- Priority support and documentation
- Access to premium features and components
- Legal protection and indemnification
- Direct access to the development team

### Pricing

Company licenses are available with flexible pricing based on your organization size and usage requirements. Contact us for custom pricing and enterprise solutions.

### FAQs

Are you not sure whether you need a Company License because of an edge case? Please contact us for clarification on specific use cases and licensing requirements.

---

For more information about licensing, pricing, and support options, please visit our website or contact us directly.